description:
Meet the newest Scarlet Speedster: Wally West, who assumes the mantle worn by his mentor Barry Allen until his sacrifice in CRISIS ON INFINITE EARTHS! In this debut issue, while on his way to deliver a heart for transplant, Wally West comes across the immortal villain Vandal Savage!

Wally West is called away from his birthday party and asked to deliver a donor heart to Science Fiction writer Eugenie Hegstrom in Seattle. Along the way, he crosses the path of Vandal Savage. Savage just killed a police investigator who getting close to figuring out who he was. After engaging him, Flash arrived at the Seattle hospital. After been put in a room to rest, Flash went into see the writer in her room after the operation. Hegstrom asked to see the costume and then thanked him. When on the plane flying back to New York City there were terrorist trying to hijack the plane Flash took care of them in 3 seconds. At his apartment Wally won the lottery and was greeted by the 50,000 year old magician Vandal Savage.

Notes:

  • Indica title is "The Flash."
  • This story has no title.
  • This story takes place in March 1987 on Wally West's 21st birthday.
  • In the "Flash" letter column a 1-1/2 page text piece by Mike Gold.

description:
Wally West's personal life with Francis Kane undergoes some changes. Meanwhile Vandal Savage continues to target the new Scarlet Speedster!

Vandal Savage appears in Wally apartment. He gets in a fight with wally and then disappears. Flash goes to the doctor to get his hand bandaged because of the fight with Vandal. Wally stays at Francine's apartment for a while. Wally collects the money he won from the lottery. Then takes Francine to the most expensive club and diner in NYC. He then finds Vandal waiting for him there. Getting into his Flash suit he saves a women from death that Savage threw from the building. From help from Francine Flash is able to defeat Vandal. He falls to his death from the building or they think. Wally buys a house for them to move into.The next morning Francine disappears.

Notes:

  • Indica title is "Flash."
  • "Who Watches the Watchmen" billboard advertisement on page 1 panel 4.
  • Cameo appearance of New York Governor Mario Cuomo congratulating Wally West on his lottery winnings.
  • Booster Gold and DC Comics symbol on the back portion of a tractor trailer on page 22 panel 3.
  • In the "Flash" letter column a 2 page text piece by Mike Gold.

description:
While testing his speed at S.T.A.R. Labs with Professor Bill Schmitz and Tina McGee, Wally encounters the destructive Kilg%re! Plus, the Flash receives a speeding ticket?!

Coming home to his new mansion, Wally West had scheduled to meet a scientist to research enhancing his speed.

After a few minutes running on the track, he encounters a machine called Kilg%re. He had startled the machine so it chased after him. When it followed him back to the base he was training at it stopped. Professor Schmitz observed Kilg%re and his finger was chopped off by the entity. Flash arrived to save him, but Kilg%re then trapped them in the warehouse. After being busted out by the army they went with Mr. Luce to meet the President via satellite. Flash then noticed something about Professor Schmitz.

Notes:

  • "Meanwhile..." one page memorial honoring the death of E. Nelson Bridwell by Dick Giordano.

description:
Wally, Tina and Professor Schmitz attempt to formulate a plan against Kilg%re! But when the techno-villain sabotages their meeting, the Flash must seek help from Cyborg!

When Flash fails to convince the U.S. government that the Kilg%re can only be defeated by shutting down the country's entire power grid, he's left to fight the bio-electric organism with help from Cyborg and Dr. Tina McGee. After one of Tina's colleagues is revealed to be a clone created by Kilg%re, Wally finds himself racing the Kilg%re through the desert to prevent the machines from merging into something much more powerful.

description:
Tina McGee decides to leave her husband for Wally West--but Jerry doesn't take the news well. Injected with a serum granting him superspeed, Jerry goes after Wally West as Speed Demon!

Tina Mcgee's husband beats her. He then goes to his lab and injects himself with steroids to make himself stronger, faster and more durable than before. After Flash finds Tina and gets her out of the city. While Tina's husband tries out his new found powers. After Wally takes her back to his mansion on Long Island Tina's husband appears again. He fights the Flash for a while and then knocks him down and grabs Tina and jumps out the window. He's blind and doesn't know where he is. He crashes into an oil depot. Flash runs after him but can't catch him in time.

description:
The Flash is on the Speed Demon's trail, but first he must ensure the safety of Tina McGee. Time to call in his friends in the Teen Titans!

After what happened before, Flash went to the oil rig and found Tina alive. They went back and Tina had to go and rest. Since Speed Demon (Tina's husband, Frank McGee) knew where their house was and was still alive they decided to go to the Titans Tower and hide out there. Beast Boy and Starfire came to pick them up at a nearby hotel. While there Flash had to look up where Speed Demon would go next using the Titans' computer. Tina told him that he would be going after the scientist that tried to put him a mental institute and also locked him out. Flash made his way in there easy, found the doctor and waited for Speed Demon. The power went out for a little while. Then he came. After engaging the Flash and he beat Speed Demon they called an ambulance. When they reached the doctor, he said that McGee's chances of survival were slim. Then he said there was only one person who could save him though and he was in the Soviet Union. Tina wanted him to go so badly. That was the Flash's next visit.

Notes:

  • The letter column's new title is "Fleet Sheet."
  • Letter to the editor from T. M. Maple.

description:
The Flash and Red Trinity take on Blue Trinity! Plus, the Guardians of the Universe summon Wally West to warn of the coming threat of the Manhunters and Wally receives some disturbing news about his father.

The Flash and Red Trinity face off against the Blue Trinity.

The Guardians call the heroes of earth together to protect the next race of immortals from the Manhunters. Unfortunately for the Flash, one of those Manhunters happens to be his father!

Notes:

  • "Read this week's issue of Millennium before reading this story."

description:
Wally West discusses his father's revelation with his therapist in Manhattan when suddenly a rotund man known as Chunk robs the diamond exchange across the street. The Flash speeds to the rescue, but Chunk has some tricks the speedster might not be prepared for!

When Wally starts seeing a therapist due to Tina they talk about his problems with his father. He tells him his father was a Manhunter. A terrified women comes in screaming. She informs them a man is raiding the jewelry store. Wally speeds out and dons his attire before anybody sees. He finds an enormous man with a gun pointing it at the manager. The Flash rushes over to the man referred to as Chunk. After engaging the man, Flash wakes up after being knocked unconscious. He charges into the hall and Chunk has vanished. Flash decides to go home. He’s disappointed. When he reaches his destination he finds the police at his home. His mom has cooked dinner and she has gotten into a fight with Tina. Next, Chunk robs another bank and disappears again. Just a big flash and then he’s gone. Another robbery by Chunk and Wally gets there faster than the speed of light. When he gets there he gets into a dispute with Chunk. Wally starts the brawl off. After a few minutes Chunk shows him how he keeps disappearing. And soon after Wally’s gone too.

description:
After vanishing with Chunk at the end of last issue, Wally wakes up in a strange dimension. There he meets fellow captives of Chunk--and a crew of cannibalistic criminals!

Trapped inside the Chunk, the Flash must battle gangs and ultimately find a way out of this place!

Notes:

  • Eric Gunderson was trapped for so long in Chunk's Void that he still thought that Barry Allen was still on trial for murder.
  • On page 16 panel 2 the wooden crate is a homage to Jack Kirby. (and Wally Wood?)

description:
Flash and the other captives attempt an escape from Chunk's barren wasteland. But when they arrive back, Wally makes a startling decision that puts him at odds with the law!

The Flash escapes from inside Chunk and finds a way to help Chester get a pardon by helping rid the city of its excess garbage problem.

Notes:

  • The cover erroneously shows that Mike Collins was the penciller but it was actually Jackson Guice.

description:
The police investigate a rash of super-speed robberies, a mysterious drug is being sold on the black market, Wally's mom and girlfriend continue to clash over house decor, and Wally discovers something interesting next door.

Thieves doped up on a super speed inducing drug called Velocity 9 attack the Red Trinity's new courier service as well as Wally's drug smuggling neighbor.

Included is DC Bonus Book #2, featuring Dr. Light with a cameo by the New Titans. Suicide Squad tie in.

Notes:

  • "Velocity 9" written by Mike Baron, penciled by Mike Collins, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, lettered by Steve Haynie and colored by Michele Wolfman.
  • "Light at the End of the Tunnel" "DC Bonus Book! No. 2" written by George Broderick Jr., penciled by Gordon Purcell, inked by Timothy Dzon, lettered by Dan McKinnon, colored by Glenn Whitmore and the consultant was Marv Wolfman.
  • Mike Gold credited as consulting editor.

description:
Vandal Savage gets in on the Velocity 9 drug racket, sending a pair of addicted hoodlums to crash a party Flash is attending--who arrive just at the moment Flash is about to lock lips with someone!

Vandal Savage goes to war against a rival drug dealer, using super speed thugs.

Notes:

  • "Publishorial" 2/3 page text piece by Jenette Kahn.
  • "DC Checklist This Week" comics released for the week.

description:
At the behest of his beautiful neighbor, Flash takes on a mission to rescue a kidnapped mob boss, only to confront immortal drug peddler and all-around bad guy Vandal Savage. Wally gets bad news about his finances.

The battle between Vandal Savage and the Flash concludes, but not until after Savage pumps the Flash full of Velocity 9!

Notes:

  • Inside joke all creator's first names were Mike.
  • Page 4 panel 2 the tractor trailer marked with Randall is a homage to the editor Barbara Randall.
  • Wally West was informed by his mother that his fortune is gone wiped out due to the stock market collapsing.
name: Wipe Out

description:
The Kapitalist Kouriers round up Velocity 9 junkies and take them to the hospital while Wally stays at home, powerless. Tension flies between Wally, his mother, and Tina while they prepare to move out of the mansion.

Messner-Loebs' run begins as Wally must deal with the fallout of his last clash with Vandal Savage. No powers, no money, suicidal velocity nine junkies and one of Savage's thugs with his own super speed and Flash costume. And what are Jerry McGee and the Chunk up to?

Notes:

  • Wally West moves to the city.
  • Mr. Gilchrist owns the block that Wally moved into.
name: Hitting Bottom

description:
Wally, Mary, and Tina go to the hospital. Tina visits with Jerry while Wally unsuccessfully attempts to entertain some children. He is saved, however, by the magic tricks of Mason Trollbridge. Returning to his apartment, Wally finds an eviction notice in his mailbox.

The Flash's problems continue, especially the ones caused when a member of the Blue Trinity shows up at the hospital!

Notes:

  • Instead of writer, penciler, inker, letterer, colorist and editor it went velocity, acceleration, momentum, overdrive, afterburn and brakes.
  • Last .75 cent issue.
name: The Adventures of Speed McGee Part 1

description:
Wally's powers return, and Jerry McGee and Flash attempt to rescue the kidnapped daughter of a man Wally simply can't stand.

Without his speed, Wally calls on one of the smartest people he knows to help track down Vandal Savage: Jerry McGee aka the Speed Demon! Did I mention Wally has been sleeping with Jerry's wife?

Notes:

  • Page 10 panel 5 the newspaper headline is "Mahlstedt Goes Bald" a homage to inker Larry Mahlstedt.
  • First $1.00 issue.
name: The Adventures of Speed McGee Part 2

description:
"The Adventures of Speed McGee" conclude, as Flash and Jerry McGee continue the search and rescue mission for the daughter of Wally's hateful landlord.

Notes:

  • Chunk has these books on his bookshelf: Whatever?, Disney Animation and The Wit and Wisdom of Elmer Fudd.
  • Barry Allen's tombstone is inscribed with "Barry Allen 1956-1985 All My Life's a Circle."

description:
The Rogues are celebrating Captain Cold's newfound freedom, but Trickster sent a invitation (as a joke) to Wally West AKA the Flash! who took it seriously and arrives at the party. And, add in the lovable Chunk.

Notes:

  • "A Meeting of Rogues" written by William Messner-Loebs, penciled by Jim Mooney, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, lettered by Steve Haynie, colored by Michele Wolfman and a special thanks to William Waldroop.
  • "Blood Ties" "Bonus Book! No. 9" (Blue Trinity) written by Hank Kanalz, penciled by Bill Knapp, inked by Jerry Acerno, lettered by Helen Vesik, colored by Matt Webb and edited by Joey Cavalieri and Joe Orlando.
  • Cover signed "Karl after Ed."
  • First post-Crisis appearance of T. O. Morrow.
  • In Blood Ties, Barry Allen 1968 flashback appearance helping Soviet fishermen to safety after their vessel was stranded in Bering Sea.

description:
The Flash and his mom are evicted from their apartment, reducing Wally to begging for money and food. As Wally roams the streets, losing his powers over the lack of food, help comes from a familiar face.

The Flash is evicted and then robbed. With no money and a growing hunger from using his super speed, Wally experiences first hand the life of a homeless person.

Notes

  • Cover artists names were signed as graffiti on the wall "Greg & Larry."
  • "Barbara Loves Karl" is a homage to Mr. and Mrs Karl Kesel.
  • "The Aliens are Coming" is a teaser to the upcoming Invasion mini-series.
  • The first post-Crisis appearance of the Pied Piper.
  • End of issue Invasion lead in story.

description:
Sent by the FBI, Flash and his pal Chunk go to Cuba where his father (a Manhunter) resides and aliens have been appearing. Fidel Castro guest stars.

Invasion kicks off with the Flash battling shape changing Durlans in Cuba.

Notes

  • Oberon snaps at Wally West when Wally calls the JLI. Oberon's outburst was due to Mary West's in-hospitality towards Blue Beetle and Booster Gold during a JLI membership drive back in Justice League International #19.
  • Last appearance of "Fleet Sheet" the title of the letter column.
  • This story takes place between Invasion #1 and Invasion #2.
  • Story continues in Manhunter #8.

description:
The Flash must free Cuba from the alien invasion! Plus, Wally West attends his 21st birthday party, which is thrown by none other than Fidel Castro.

The Flash had spent much of the Invasion protecting the innocent citizens of Cuba. This has unexpected after-effects, including Fidel Castro romancing his mother!

Notes:

  • This issue takes place in March on Wally West's 21st birthday.
  • First appearance of "Speed Reading" the new title of the letter column.
  • This story takes place betweenInvasion #2 and Invasion #3.
  • Story continues from Manhunter #8.
  • Story concludes in Manhunter #9.

description:
Tina McGee, Mason Trollbridge, and others try and help Wally get his speed back, including interviewing Lois Lane and Joan Garrick about their respective husbands: Superman and the original Flash!

Tina and Jerry McGee attempt to restore Wally West's super-speed, which he lost to the Durlan gene bomb during the Invasion event. Despite Tina's doubts, their experiment is a success, but Wally's first test run is a disaster. He takes off at such high speed that he causes a devastating sonic boom and leaves a trail of scorched earth behind him.

Notes:

  • Cat Grant and Clark Kent cameo on page 2 panel 2?

description:
Looking for a vacation, the Flash heads to Paris--but instead ends up in Casablanca! There, he must stop an assassination attempt on a Russian scientist by the villains Merlyn and Syonide!

Wally West tries to use his JLE teleporter to escape a dreary day of housework with a trip to Paris. However, he ends up in Lisbon instead, and quickly stumbles into the middle of a plot to assassinate a defecting Russian scientist and his escort, Phantom Lady. Flash helps Phantom Lady and the scientist escape from a run-down diner, and finds himself being forced to take the two of them on a tour of Portugal's worst restaurants. It turns out that the scientist's research involves the poisoning of food supplies, and he has come to Portugal to collect some new samples. The trio finally arrives at the airport to escape the country, but first they have to fight off the would-be assassins Merlyn and Syonide one more time.

Notes:

  • Guest creators.
  • Cameo appearance of the Justice League Europe members on the splash page.
  • First appearance of the Justice League International Embassy of Lisbon, Portugal.
  • Poison Gas Arrow used.

description:
The Flash goes on a date with Connie Noleski, but a shootout at the movie theater could have Wally rethinking his current position in life.

Wally West takes his girlfriend to the movies. As the movie begins Wally notices that the images on the screen seem to freeze. He realizes that he has involuntarily gone into super speed mode. That is when he feels something pressing on the back of his neck. It is a bullet.

He hears a small crack and figures out that someone is still shooting a gun. So now he has to run around the darkened movie theater trying to find each bullet before they find their targets.

Notes:

  • First appearance of the Justice League International Embassy in Rome.
  • Mr. Maxwell worked at the embassy.
  • Power Girl cameo appearance.
  • The movies Batman, One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest and Cool Hand Luke were playing at the movie theater Wally and Connie went to on a date.

description:
Captured by the Turtle, the Flash is subjected to sensory deprivation experiments, forcing Wally to face his inner fears--including those involving his mentor Barry Allen!

Wally West has been captured by the Turtle and subjected to a sensory deprivation experiment. Trapped in a seemingly endless white space, Wally begins flashing back to the events of Invasion, then hallucinates Barry Allen berating him for his performance as the Flash. Wally fights off his delusions, but exhausts himself doing so, allowing the Turtle to move in for the kill.

Notes:

  • Except for the Turtle and Wally West all other characters appeared in Wally's hallucinations.

description:
With the Flash captured, Mason assembles a team of Wally's friends and searches for the Scarlet Speedster. Can this mismatched ensemble find the missing hero and out step the Turtle?

As the Turtle holds Wally West in a stasis field in his base below Keystone City, Mason Trollbridge assembles a group of Wally's friends to search for him. At first the mismatched group seems to be making a mess of things, but one-by-one they reveal that they have actually been putting on a show to fool the Turtle. The defeated villain blows up his own headquarters (and possibly himself) leaving his abused assistant Turtle-Man to take the fall--and finally get credit for his role in the Turtle's schemes.
name: Behold the Turtle!

description:
"Running on the Edge." Wally enjoys a backyard barbecue and some television with girlfriend Connie and other friends, but must leave the scene to go after terrorists. Wally's future wife Linda Park continues to get more "screen time."

Notes:

  • This story takes place one week after the last issue.
  • Tina and Jerry McGee got a job in Central City.
  • A crate containing the Justice League Transporter Tube arrives at Wally West's place.
  • Linda Park goes undercover to investigate Lila McGrath's Center for the Advanced Life Enhancement.
  • The new Flash logo was created by Steve Bove.
name: Running on the Edge

description:
"Channels of Love...and Fear!" Wally visits the Celestial Ranch, a new age self help center. There he discovers an under cover Linda Park working on an exposé of the place.

Notes:

  • Captain Barrow was placed in charge of the 49th precinct due to the recent death of Daniel Phillips.
  • Tina and Jerry McGee are working at Central University on artificial intelligence.
  • Cameo flashback appearance of Wally West as Porcupine Man.
  • Cameo flashback appearance of Barry Allen.

"Elemental Conflict." Flash appears on Linda's television show as an interviewee. Linda gets more than she bargained for when Flash rescues hostages as part of his live act. Flash then battles Dr. Alchemy.

description:
"Mechanical Difficulty." Tina McGee is working to the point of sheer exhaustion and appears to be losing her mind as she's menaced by a mechanical, well, menace. Flash and future wife Linda Park proceed to pay Tina a visit. Linda's jealousy over Connie is the first hint that maybe she is beginning to like Wally as more than a friend.

Notes:

description:
Vixen is calming a jackal by feeding him maternal scent when all of a sudden a pack of dogs and cats rush her and knock her to the ground. It is at this time that Gorilla Grodd appears holding a battered and bruised Wally West by the hair. Vixen replicates Grodd's scent and gains his strength, she loses control and almost kills him, she throws Grodd through a wall where he retreats to his makeshift laboratory. Meanwhile, they take the injured Flash to a safe house to heal. There they concoct a plan to try and defeat Grodd and Wally calls Pied Piper.

Grodd on completion of his machine gains control of all the animals in Keystone City and sets them on the public. Vixen, uses Grodd's scent to find out where he is and they set out to find him only to have Vixen lose control and attack the Pied Piper AND Wally! Grodd captures the two (Wally and Piper) and locks them up like animals.

The animals Grodd is controlling, having gained an equal brain capacity to Grodd's start to feel as though they are entitled to some of the power also. This is where we meet "Rex" and the book ends.

Notes:

  • Amanda Waller, Bronze Tiger and Batman cameo flashback appearances.
  • Page 21 panel 1 Novic- Blvd is a homage to Irv Novick.
  • The cover is a homage to the cover of The X-Men #100.

description:
"Savage Season." Immortal villain Vandal Savage, who has set up a classic, "Barry Allen style trap" for Wally, shows up at Wally's house looking very old.

Notes:

  • Cameo flashback of Conrad Bortz injecting Velocity 9 into Vandal Savage from The Flash #14.
  • Wally West used a resetted JLA Teleporter to be teleported to the Egyptian Embassy in search of Vandal Savage.
  • Wally West was shot by Vandal Savage.
name: Savage Season

description:
"The Fastest Man-Alive!" A "dead" Wally West encounters friends and Vandal Savage in the "afterlife." Vandal Savage's personal assistant becomes Lady Flash. Star Labs creates a new costume for Wally.

Notes:

  • Wally West, Vandal Savage, Lady Savage, Immortal Man, Gil Barrow, Benjamin Hughes, Mary West, Tina and Jerry McGee appeared in the story. The other characters appeared in a dream sequence.
  • Wally West has a new costume.
  • Lady Savage was given a stolen Flash costume.

description:
The race is on for the dynamic duo of Superman and the Fastest Man Alive to save Jimmy Olsen.

The Pied Piper comes out to Wally as gay.

Notes:

  • On page 18 panel 1 Swan Pl and Boring St are a homage to Curt Swan and Wayne Boring.

description:
"The Return of Barry Allen" part 1! Barry Allen has apparently returned from the dead, but his successor--current Flash Wally West--is somewhat skeptical. Regardless, the two speedsters must team up to prevent an assassination attempt on a mob boss!

Wally and Linda West, Jay and Joan Garrick and Hal Jordan are having a New Years Eve party when Barry Allen, who is suppose to be dead shows up at their door. After Hal's ring proves it is Barry, he explains that a week ago he found himself in Central City lost and confused and it wasn't until he saw the Flash Museum that he knew who he was. Hal believes him but needs to go, promising that Barry being back would be a secret. After Hal leaves Barry sees the Pied Piper on the street and attacks him. Barry has to explain to Barry that the Piper is now a good guy and that things have changed. He is about to explain more but Wally gets a call that there is a hit on "Handsome Jack" Giacomo. Barry and Wally leave Jay behind and rush to help.

The two Flashes catch the three hit-men and save Handsome Jack, but Wall is still unsure if he is truly happy that Barry is back and if he even believes it is Barry. Before they take the hit-men to jail Barry freaks out and leaves Wally. Barry runs to Iris's grave and apologizes that only he came back, this is where Wally finds him and tells him that now he trusts Barry again.
name: Trust

description:
The Fastest Men Alive and three generations of Flashes--Wally West, Barry Allen, and Jay Garrick--team up to take down some high-tech punks, but when the normally levelheaded Barry loses his temper, Wally becomes even more skeptical of his return. "The Return of Barry Allen" part 2."

Wally West and Jay Garrick are trying to stop a train heist by The Combine, a gang hired by the new mysterious crime boss of Central City. It looks like the two Flashes have it under control but one on the gang derails the train and Jay and Wally have to try and save the bystanders in the way. Then Barry Allen shows up to stop the train before it hits PS114, then takes all the credit.

Wally feels okay with this and later tells Linda, that he is thinking of moving to Midway City or change his name, but they are interrupted by police Chief Hotchkiss and Jay calling to tell him the C.C.P.D. found the Combine's hideout. Wally leaves Linda to find Barry and meet up with Jay at the hideout. He finds Barry wondering the streets, and after a quick talk the three speedsters head to the hideout.

At the hideout the Flashes try to figure out how to handle the situation when the Combine attacks them. Jay get taken out by a ray gun and Wally gets buried under a collapsed wall, to which one of the gang yells "I killed the Flash". Upon hearing this Barry goes crazy and almost kills the man but Wally, who was just shaken, has to stop him.

When he stops Barry he is shocked to hear that Barry was angrynot because Wally could be dead but because he feels he is the only Flash.

description:
Barry Allen and Wally West team up to take down the Combine but Wally still remains skeptical that Barry is the real thing. Featuring the re-introduction of another old-school speedster--Max Mercury! "The Return of Barry Allen" part 3.

Wally West is still reeling from the idea that Barry Allen is back from the dead and that Barry wants to be the one and only Flash. Wally is still not sure what that means for him and Central City. While trying to figure out what to do, Wally gets a letter from his friend the Pied Piper informing him that the Combine, the latest super gang in Central City, have there headquarters in Broome Building, 26th floor.

Wally quickly finds Barry and the pair of Flashes rush to the building where they find a scale model of the city and a member of the Combine. He tells them that the Combine will Central city and the first step is to get rid of the speedsters. When Barry blindly attacks him he triggers a force field that traps the heroes. Barry can't vibrate through it and it begins to shrink around them.

Wally uses his quick thinking to help Barry vibrate through but, Barry leaves Wally trapped. After Barry just leaves Wally to die, Wally tries a new trick and gets out too. When Wally gets home he hears Barry on the news tell all of Central City that the Flash is dead.

Meanwhile, Jay is putting together a team of Speedsters, that include Max Mercury and Johnny Quick, for some mysterious life or death mission.
name: Identity Crisis

description:
Jay Garrick, Max Mercury and Johnny Quick team up to try and bring down the man who claims to be a returned-from-the-grave Barry Allen, but whose recent behavior has proved that's a lie! "The Return of Barry Allen" part 4.

Wally West is still reeling from the fact that Barry Allen is back from the dead and that his former idle left him for dead in a Combine deathtrap. And now Wally learns that Barry is battling Hal Jordan, and destroying the Flash Museum. Wally isn't sure what to do but luckily Jay Garrick formed his own team to stop Barry.

While Barry is trying to kill some of Central City's citizens, Jay, Johnny Quick and Max Mercury save the day. Barry throws a handful of gravel at Johnny injuring him and hits Max with an I-beam while he is trying to save a construction worker. Barry then causes a helicopter to fall on Jay while he is trying to save the crew.

Meanwhile, Wally walks the streets and finds himself in the alley that Barry found himself in when he returned from the dead. there is finds a book that has Iris's name in and learns the secret of the Barry Allen impostor.
name: Suicide Run

description:
The real identity of the impostor revealed! The man who is supposedly Barry Allen organizes a prison break to assemble an army and take down the city. It's up to Wally West to stop him and solve the mystery of the fake Flash. "The Return of Barry Allen" part 5.

Wally West now knows that the real Barry Allen is still dead and the man who is posing as his uncle is faster then Wally, so Johnny Quick tries to teach him his formula. Max Mercury tries to teach him the Zen of Speed. but it is Jay Garrick that shows him that the way to be faster is inside of Wally. Wally then tells the other who Barry really is but he needs their help to prove it. Wally runs off to the Flash Museum and the rest go to find Barry.

The Barry imposter has gone to Central City State Penitentiary, to release and arm the convicts inside. Luckily Jay, Max and Johnny show up before anyone gets hurt. During the fight Jay tears the symbol off Barry costume forcing him to flee back to the Flash Museum where Wally is waiting for him.

Wally throws the fake Barry a Flash ring and tells him he found the book he had dropped, The Life of Barry Allen. Realizing the gig is up the fake Barry reveals is is really Professor Zoom
name: Blitzkrieg

description:
Wally finds out everything about the so called Barry Allen, but what will Wally do about it?

Wally West has proven that Professor Zoom is the fake Barry Allen, but the Zoom that faces Wally now is not the same man that killed Iris. Eobard reveals that he is from the future and that he saw Barry as a hero and even had surgery to look like Barry and stole the Cosmic Treadmill. He then gave himself super speed and came the the 20th century to meet Barry Allen. But something went wrong and he arrived years after Barry's death. He went to the Flash Museum where he learned that he was going to become the man that killed Iris and was going to be killed by Barry. Eobard went crazy and thought that he was Barry Allen. When he remembered who he was he deduced the only way to survive was to stay in the present and become Barry Allen.

Eobard is about to kill Wally when Max Mercury, Johnny Quick and Hal Jordan arrive and force Eobard to run away. They take Wally to the hospital where Jay Garrick is laid up. Then they see on the news that Eobard is attacking Linda and Wally rushes off to save her. This time beats Wally up and forces him to chase after. But Wally has a plan and tricks Eobard into thinking that he used the treadmill to kill Eobard as a baby.

Eobard uses the treadmill to stop Wally but is launched into the future with no memory of where he was and Wally reveals he just hid.

Epilogue: The book The Life of Barry Allen was written by Iris Allen three years later.
name: The Once and Future Flash

description: A Zero Hour crossover issue. The Flash Family is working with the newly arrived Bart Allen at Iris West’s house. Linda Park is on the run from the cult of Kobra, who want to silence her after she probed into their local actions. Argus feeds Linda and Flash information on Kobra’s current whereabouts, and Flash investigates. As Flash spies on Kobra, Bart Allen appears on the scene, forcing Flash’s hand. Flash and Impulse deal with Kobra’s men, but then are drawn into an ambush by Abra Kadabra. As Flash faces Kadabra, the two are suddenly hit with a time flux. Flash and Kadabra find themselves in Kadabra’s native time: the 64th century. Once there, they see a temporal rift, and are approached by Waverider.
name: Reckless Youth, Part Three: Just Do It

description:
A ZERO HOUR tie-in issue! Trapped in the Speed Force, Wally West finds himself leaping through time as an intangible presence, observing key moments in his life. Can he escape and get back to his present? And how does his joining with the Speed Force change him? Events of this issue lead into FLASH #95!

A Zero Month crossover issue. While trying to outrun the time rift from Zero Hour #4, the Flash finds himself absorbed into the Speed Force. He finds himself moving uncontrollable through time, yet intangible to his surroundings. His first stop is to a recent battle with Team Turmoil, where he finds Max Mercury mysteriously watching over him. Other stops include him becoming the Flash, him finding out about Barry Allen’s death, him forming the Teen Titans, him gaining his powers, and him arguing with his parents. For his last stop, though, he finds himself tangible, and at a pivotal scene in his past where he first dreamed of being a hero. Our Flash convinces young Wally that his whole life is ahead of him. Feeling sure of himself, Flash starts controlling the Speed Force, forcing it to propel him back to the proper time.
name: Flashing Back

description:
With Flash gone, Linda Park, Impulse, Jesse Quick, Jay Garrick and Max Mercury attempt to thwart Kobra's plans.

Notes:

  • Both newstand and deluxe foil covers penciled by Mike Wieringo and inked by Jose Marzan Jr.
  • 48 page issue.
  • On page 18 panel 3 the army soldier's name tag is Augustyn as a homage to Brian Augustyn.

description: Final Night crossover. "Pray for the Dawn," a tie-in issue to The Final Night. The world is freezing, thanks to a being called the Sun-Eater, and Linda and Wally argue about just how much the public should know. Flash battles a group of survivalists called The Last Hope Militia.

description: Asked by the city fathers to leave Keystone City and take the destruction of his super-heroic presence with him, Wally heads west to sunny California and the town of Santa Marta, which can't wait to claim the Flash as its resident super-hero. But Linda Park isn't willng to uproot her entire life & career to follow Wally to his new hometown.

description:
Keystone City doesnt want him, but Santa Marta, California is all too happy to have Flash as its resident super-hero, making Wally West the "Flash of Two Cities"... with a raft of new & deadly challenges awaiting him in his new base of operations.

Notes:

  • The cover is a homage of the cover of The Flash #123.
name: The Flash of Two Cities

description:
The Flash's Rogues Gallery are back, but with Flash prohibited from operating in Keystone, who will save the city from their deadly rampage?

Part 1 of "Hell to Pay." The last time we saw the members of the Rogues Gallery was at their deaths in Underworld Unleashed, but now they're back... soulless, conscienceless monsters who have conquered Keystone City. But with Flash prohibited from operating in Keystone, who will save the city from their deadly rampage?
name: Hell Breaks Loose

description:
Flash returns to Keystone City to take on the menace of the soulless Rogue's Gallery that are intent on destroying first his city.

Part 2 of "Hell To Pay" guest starring the JLA as Flash goes to hell literally to deal with Neron, then returns to Keystone City to take on the soulless Rogues Gallery intent on destroying first his city and then... him!

To prevent this, Flash enlists the aid of Jay Garrick, Impulse & Max Mercury to make it appear that the Scarlet Speedster is still in control. But The Suit sees through this charade and takes the opportunity to finish off Flash once & for all.

description:
Mirror Master ambushes Wally at Linda Park's home.  He's trapped her in a mirror dimension and if the Flash doesn't do something about it in the next fifteen minutes, she'll be stuck there forever.

Unfortunately for Wally, Mirror Master's illusions are enough to fool him into running through a prism at the speed of light.  This splits the Flash into seven different colored versions.  By the time the Flash can escape Mirror Master's trap, McCulloch has already robbed the Keystone National Bank.

Mirror Master continues to hold off the Flash with illusions and mirror duplicates but the Flash manages to break McCulloch's gun...without which Linda will be trapped forever.  Mirror Master sends the Flash to Singapore to pick up replacement parts and then he frees Linda with one minute to spare...or so he says.  Wally is given the choice to catch the crook or make sure his girlfriend is alright.

Flash chooses to check on Linda but after finding her to be okay, he runs back and catches the Mirror Master.  McCulloch laughs, knowing he can escape his cell no problem...until the Flash turns out the lights.
name: Through the looking Glass!

description: Filling in for Wally while he recuperates from the injuries he suffered in the battle with The Suit, Jay Garrick spends a typical day in Keystone City, lunching with friends, battling super-villains, keeping a date with his wife for their anniversary... and fighting the clock to save the life of an old foe turned friend.
name: Still Life in the Fast Lane

description: "The Human Race Part One: Radio Days." After G-Force crash lands in Keystone to warn The Flash, a pair of hostile aliens force Wally to race Kwyzz, a strange childhood friend of his that came through the radio from another world. The stakes are the destruction of earth itself should Wally loose.

description:
Wally West recruits Max Mercury, Jay Garrick, Bart "Impulse" Allen, and Jesse Quick to assist him in traveling the time stream to prevent two future Flashes and Barry Allen from falling prey to Cobalt Blue's mystic gem.

Chain Lightning, part 1 of 6. Flash Wally West has discovered that the villain Cobalt Blue is actually Barry Allen’s twin brother Malcolm Thawne. Just as Barry Allen and the Flash mantle will be handed down through the generations, so will the Thawne family and the Cobalt Blue mantle, through Cobalt Blue’s mystic gem. Wally finds out that, between now and the 30th century, two Flashes will fall to Cobalt Blue. Wally decides to rally the troops and send them through the timeline to warn the Flashes of each generation. Wally recruits Jay Garrick while fighting Turmoil 13 in Keystone City, Jesse Quick from her company Quick Start Enterprises, and Max Mercury and Impulse from their lives Manchester. Wally keeps Malcolm Thawne trapped in a vibrational prison under the watchful eye of Central City forensics expert Angela Margolin. The five speedsters split up, traveling across the timestream to warn the Flash legacy. Jesse Quick arrives in the year 2764, where the Flash of that era, Jace Allen, is fighting that era’s incarnation of Cobalt Blue. Just as Jesse and Jace regroup, Jesse is enveloped by Cobalt Blue’s blue flame.
name: Chain Lightning, Chapter One: The Gathering Storm

description:
Wally West, Jay Garrick, Max Mercury, and Jesse Quick run into a variety of speedsters as they travel the time stream looking to save the lives of future Flashes.

Chain Lightning, part 2 of 6. Each of the speedsters have traveled to another time period to recruit heroes against Cobalt Blue. Jesse Quick had come to the 28th century, and been blasted by that era’s Cobalt Blue. That era’s Flash, Jace Allen, saves her, and the two team up to defeat the female green-skinned Cobalt Blue. Jesse gives Jace a sliver of Cobalt Blue’s gem to Jace before heading off again. In the 853rd century, Wally West stops by to recruit the help of that era’s Flash, John Fox, member of the Justice Legion Alpha. The two Flashes defeat the villain Wetware, Wally gives John a sliver, and the two are off to continue warning speedsters. Max Mercury arrives in the year 2231, where he is not in time to stop the Flash of that era from killing Cobalt Blue. Earlier, that era’s Cobalt Blue crippled that Flash’s daughter. Unfortunate, a nearby teen grabs the mystic gem, becoming the next Cobalt Blue and killing Flash. Max realizes that the gem is what passes the Cobalt Blue dynasty. The teen Cobalt Blue is defeated by Max and the Flash’s daughter, Sela, now powered by the Speed Force. Sela becomes the next Flash, but the curse of Cobalt Blue took its first of two Flashes. Sela and Max continue the recruitment. Meanwhile, Bart finds his next Flash, Jay Garrick finds his next Flash ( Wally’s daughter), and Wally West goes to confront the Reverse-Flash.
name: Chain Lightning, Chapter Two: Time Like a River

description: Chain Lightning, part 3 of 6. Each of the speedsters have traveled to another time period to recruit heroes against Cobalt Blue. Wally West has come to the 25th century to find out what connection Malcolm Thawne, the first Cobalt Blue, has with Eobard Thawne, the Reverse-Flash. However, when he gets there, he finds Reverse-Flash the “hero” and Chardaq Allen the “villain,” having been possessed by the spirit of Cobalt Blue. Wally, Reverse-Flash, and the Central City Police Force, headed by Simogyn Allen, defeat this era’s Cobalt Blue. However, Reverse-Flash escapes police custody via the Cosmic Treadmill. In the 21st century, Jay Garrick and that era’s Kid Flash, Iris West, defeat that era’s Cobalt Blue, and both continue to recruit throughout the timestream. Bart Allen recruits Thondor Allen, his era’s Flash, and comes across another Flash recruiting. At this point, most of the Flashes between the 20th and 30th centuries are passing along both information and slivers of Cobalt Blue’s mystic gem. Back in the 20th century, though, the original Cobalt Blue almost blasts his guard, Central City PD member Angela Margolin, but Jay Garrick saves her. Meanwhile, Wally follows Reverse-Flash to the year 2980, where he meets a Thawne plotting to kill the Tornado Twins.
name: Chain Lightning, Chapter Three: Shooting the Rapids

description:
Even more speedsters join the fight as Wally meets with Iris West II, as well Don and Dawn Allen, a.k.a the Tornado Twins.

Chain Lightning, part 4 of 6. Each of the speedsters have traveled to another time period to recruit heroes against Cobalt Blue. Wally West has followed Reverse-Flash to the year 2980, where he has uncovered a plan for one of the Cobalt Blues to kill the Tornado Twins. Wally stops Reverse-Flash from getting his hands on Cobalt Blue’s mystic gem, and returns Reverse-Flash to 25th century jail. Meanwhile, Flashes from all eras coordinate efforts against various Cobalt Blues, all the while passing along information and slivers of Cobalt Blue’s gem. Wally swings by the early 30th century, where he meets up with the Tornado Twins, Don and Dawn Allen, to confirm they are OK. They have already received word and their slivers, so Wally continues on. Bart Allen travels to the 30th century to warn his cousin Jenni Ognats, XS of the Legion of Super-Heroes. Bart thinks that XS is under attack, but he has mistakenly interrupted Legion tryouts. Bart and XS meet the 21st century Kid Flash, Iris West, and the three decide to go to the 30th century era where Barry Allen is still alive. When they arrive, they fight each other. Wally also arrives, and realizes the desire to fight is coming from the slivers. Realizing they have all been tricked, Wally tries to free the three teenagers. However, he is interrupted by all the Flashes, all controlled by Cobalt Blue, led by a possessed Jay Garrick. Just as everything looks hopeless, Wally is rescued by the 30th century Barry Allen.
name: Chain Lightning, Chapter Four: Undertow

description:
Cobalt Blue uses fragments of his splintered magical crystal to possess an army of super speedsters, which Wally and Barry must battle.

Chain Lightning, part 5 of 6. In the 30th century, Cobalt Blue has possessed Jay Garrick, and is controlling a couple of dozen super-speedsters spanning ten centuries. The only two speedsters with their free will left are Wally West and Barry Allen. The two heroes try to stand against the speedster army, but only last so long. They two flee to the Flash Museum, where they use some of Mirror Master’s old gear to go invisible. After regrouping, the two Flashes use the Rogues Gallery’s gear to free Jay Garrick from Cobalt Blue’s possession. The three original Flashes then combine their super-speed to generate vibrations that shatter the other speedsters’ gem slivers, freeing them. The other speedsters leave, freed, while Wally West spends one last minute with Barry Allen. However, Cobalt Blue is not dead, but still exists as a living flame. Cobalt Blue arises, and kills Barry Allen. Wally is too shocked to move. With Barry dead, though, history changes. Without Barry to stop the Anti-Monitor’s tachyon cannon during the Crisis of Infinite Earths, the Anti-Monitor has now won.
name: Chain Lightning, Chapter Five: Whirlpool

description:
As "Chain Lightning" concludes, in failing to prevent the untimely death of Barry Allen, Wally West has inadvertently changed history--leading to a battle against the Anti-Monitor!

Chain Lightning, part 6 of 6. With the death of Barry Allen in the 30th century, history has changed. Now, Wally West finds himself in a 30th century where the Anti-Monitor has won the Crisis on Infinite Earths. After trying to fight the Anti-Monitor alone, Wally runs back into the past, to join forces with the rest of the heroes during the Crisis on Infinite Earths. He joins forces with Superman’s assault team on the Anti-Monitor’s base of operations. Even with the Flash helping out invisibly, the heroes still fall to the Anti-Monitor. Realizing that the only way for the heroes to win is to bring back Barry Allen, Wally goes to the point where Cobalt Blue kills Barry. Wally intercepts Cobalt Blue before he kills Barry, and uses his speed to destroy both Cobalt Blue and himself. Wally West has joined the Speed Force alongside Barry Allen and Johnny Quick, but a new, mysterious Flash has appeared on in Keystone City.

description: A new logo, a new costume and a new(?) Flash begin a startling new era for the Fastest Man Alive! There's a super-fast stranger in town, and he's calling himself the Flash. But who is this world-weary, battle-scarred hero in a fearsome, nearly all-black costume? He doesn't play by the rules of Keystone's heroes or its villains, and he's darker, nastier, and wilder than any Flash Keystone City has ever seen before. This Flash has somehow earned the trust of Golden Age Flash Jay Garrick... is he someone we've seen before? And what about Wally West?
name: New Kid in Town

description: The adventures of the mysterious Flash continue a startling new era for the man who calls himself the Fastest Man Alive! The new, darker Flash is having a hard time convincing the usual cast of characters that he's a good guy, after all, he won't say who he is and won't answer any questions about Wally West! But it may all be moot if he can't stop the newest foe in Flash's Rogues Gallery: the Folded Man!

description: The mystery of the new Flash deepens as the riddle of Linda Park's whereabouts comes closer to being solved! While Max Mercury, Impulse and Jesse Quick try to learn the secret identity of the would-be Flash, the new hero and Angela Margolin are trapped within the confines of the Folded Man! Meanwhile, the strangely forgotten Linda Park fights her way out of a trap...but a trap set by whom?

Things were pretty wild with one new Flash, but this issue's got three Flashes, each one facing a unique death trap! Who the heck are these guys, anyway?

description:
It's the shocking issue readers have been waiting for as the final fate of Linda Park is revealed and her role in Flash history is assured!
 
 Flash has just proposed to Angela and they are hoping to enjoy a romantic time in Venice, but Replicant has other plans for them.  Flash is forced to try and save her from his evil tricks.  Meanwhile, back in Central City, the rest of the Flash's are trying to figure out what Impulse is talking about... Linda?  Kadabra?  Is he seeing ghosts, making up stories?
name: Setting The Stage

description: Abra Kadabra has begun capturing all the Earth's speedsters! He's already nabbed Impulse, Jay Garrick, Max Mercury, and Jesse Quick, and now there's only one Speed Forcer left: Wally West, the Flash! But when Abra sends his henchman, the one-man Rogues' Gallery called Replicant, after the Scarlet Speedster, it sparks a development that readers will be talking about for months!
name: Reverse Flash

description:
A special issue guest-starring the original JSA! Last issue, we saw Flash Wally West's honeymoon. Now, it's Golden Age Flash Jay Garrick's turn to share the story of his own post-wedding adventure in late-1940s Las Vegas! There're guest-stars all over the joint, including Jay's old teammates, the Justice Society of America!

This is another "Flashback" issue. Jay Garrick tells for the first time his recollections about his honeymoon night.

Newlyweds Jay and Joan Garrick think that they will spend a quiet honeymoon in a little known town called Las Vegas, Nevada. However, the other members of the Justice Society of America track the Garricks to their motel room. The JSA members ask the Garricks to join them for a fun wedding reception at the Blue Heron Hotel and Casino. Joan declines, and Jay reluctantly joins the JSA members.

The celebration at the Blue Heron Hotel and Casino turns into a rescue mission. When Jay steps out of the reception temporarily to check on his wife, several of the Flash's old enemies turn up to rob the casino. The JSA members fall to these unexpected foes. Can the Flash save the day?
name: Honeymoon in Vegas

description:
New cover artist Brian Bolland (THE INVISIBLES, BATMAN: THE KILLING JOKE) makes his debut in Part 1 of the 6-part "Wonderland." His connection to the Speed Force severed, Wally West finds himself jailed in a world that claims there never has been any hero who called himself the Flash. But some things seem oddly familiar...

The Flash wakes up in the Keystone Police Department where he is being handcuffed for the murder of a police officer. Wally tries to escape but realizes he no longer possesses super speed. Just as the cops (including Fred Chyre and Mick Rory, mysteriously a cop instead of a crook) are about to knock him out, a bulletin comes on the TV, announcing the tenth anniversary of Aquaman's death.

When the Flash comes to, he is locked in a holding cell. A woman who claims to be a social worker offers him a glass of water and asks to hear his story. West recounts the origin of the Flash before realizing he has been drugged. The woman tells him that he has been given a tranquilizer and truth serum, that he is delusional, not a superhero.

While questioning his own sanity, Wally discovers that he still has his lightning marked wedding ring and thus cannot be crazy. Looking out the window, he sees a blonde man running late for an appointment. Recognizing his mentor, Barry Allen, Wally calls out to him and attempts to phase through the prison walls but fails.

Officer Rory comes to investigate the noise but he is shot from off panel by Captain Cold. Cold decapitates Rory and shatters the frozen cell bars, freeing the Flash.
name: Wonderland, Chapter One: Lightning in a Bottle

description:
Wally West struggles to puzzle out a world with no Flashes in Part 2 of the 6-part "Wonderland." Captain Cold tries to break Wally out of a Central City jail, but the former Fastest Man Alive finds life on the outside even harder to take than the beatings he endured in custody: Barry Allen alive, Wally's allies dead, a world in many ways the reverse of his own...what gives?

Cold seems to be the only one who remembers the Flash. Together, the two succeed in busting out of the Keystone PD but not before Wally fails to prevent Cold from killing another police officer.

The Flash realizes this must be an alternate universe and to get his powers back, he has to find the man who started it all: Jay Garrick. The pair flee, their escape covered by a mysterious silver clad sniper named Plunder who is apparently working for the Thinker.

West and Cold arrive at Joan Garrick's home to find that she is married to another man, an abusive drunk at that. They handle the punk and leave, taking with them the a book entiled "The Death of the Hero" and the knowledge of Jay Garrick's location.

They find Jay, or rather his grave. According to Joan, he died a hero, joining the army after recovering from his jab accident, the accident that was supposed to give him super speed. In this world, the Flash never existed. The book they retrieved tells the whole story. The Justice Society fought in World War II but without the original Flash to save him, Mr. Terrific was KIA, sparking the decision to drop the atomic bomb on Berlin. Germany was completely annihilated and the JSA retired in shame.

Later, the JLA arrived but because Barry Allen wasn't with them, Aquaman was killed by Starro, causing rampant prejustice against aliens, depriving the earth of many heroes. Aqualad refused to give up but the Teen Titans were also slaughtered on an early mission (by Mister Twister) because of their missing speedster, Kid Flash.

Cold takes the Flash up on a hill that overlooks Central City. Years ago, Shade, Fiddler and Thinker had a war over the city but without the Flash to stop them, it was all but demolished. Wally realizes that those villains had actually fought over Keystone, not Central. Also, Cold, usually right handed, has been holding his gun with his left hand. The two realize that they are trapped in a mirror world but before they can do anything about it, they find themselves under attack by more cops including West's mentor, Barry Allen.
name: Wonderland, Chapter Two: The Lightning Rod

description:
Robin and Aqualad guest-star in a flashback issue written by Joe Casey (Cable, WILD TIMES: GEN13), with art by Duncan Rouleau and Aaron Sowd! After the extra-special issue #150, Waid, Augustyn, Pelletier, and Russell take a one-issue break, so they just provide a framing sequence for this tale from early in Wally West's career, when he and a pal from his neighborhood had to head off an attempted Gorilla City invasion of America!

Fifteen year old Wally West discovers a gorilla lurking inside the Blue Valley, Nebraska, Museum of Humanities after the museum should be closed for the evening. Transforming into Kid Flash, he confronts the gorilla. Kid Flash discovers that Gorilla Montague is not an enemy. Montague is a good guy and not evil, unlike Gorilla Grodd. Montague is attempting to retrieve a simian skull stolen from an ancestral burial ground in the Congo near Gorilla City. Montague warns Kid Flash that he is on a mission to prevent a war between Gorilla City and the United States over the stolen gorilla remains. Respecting gorilla people's indigenous rights, Kid Flash decides to help Montague return the simian remains to Africa. But they must overcome several travel problems, time constraints, and thwart adventurer Buck Wargo who claims to be the rightful owner of the simian skull.

Reprinted in DC Goes Ape #1.
name: Kid Flash in Territorealis

description:
Overview

New regular penciller Scott Kolins joins as a new chapter in Wally West's life begins. The Flash comes to the horrifying conclusion that many people he's come into contact with and rescued over the years are being systematically murdered. Making matters worse, his ex-girlfriend Frances Kane -- Magenta -- has returned to plague him.

description:
Every time he thinks he's out, they pull him back in - the Pied Piper, that is! As if Piper weren't in enough trouble already, the Joker's venomous plans strike Keystone City, transforming one of the Flash's greatest allies into a lethal, laughing Rogue! Plus, Iron Heights is under siege and a "Jokerized" Deadshot sets his sights on Captain Boomerang!

Deadline, Merlyn and Deadshot are coming to Keystone with smiles on their faces. The Flash must stop them from killing themselves and everyone around them as well.
name: Smile for the Camera

description:
In "Absolute Zero," the Flash faces a difficult situation regarding one of his Rogues. Captain Cold may be a thief...but is he a murderer? Find out when Cold single-handedly tracks down the killer of someone very near and dear to him.

Notes:

  • Ranked #22 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".

description:
A Rogues spotlight issue taking a look into the life, origin and current status of the Pied Piper! Many of the other Rogues' lives center around this updated villain, including Trickster-turned-FBI agent James Jesse, and all-out Rogue Heat Wave!

The Pied Piper, a reformed member of the Rogue's Gallery, is on the run from the law. A few months previous, both of his parents were murdered, and he is the prime suspect. He seeks help from his reformed friends, the Trickster and Heat Wave. The Flash is searching for the Piper also.

deck: The Cheetah has come to Keystone City in search of the man she believes can teach her to be faster: Zoom, the Reverse-Flash! And where the Cheetah is, Wonder Woman can't be far behind!
description:
Part 1 of 2 Zoom and Cheetah want to make Flash and Wonder Woman better heroes.

Boston- Minerva, the current Cheetah, convinces Dr. Zolomon, the current Zoom to help her learn how to increase her speed.

Keystone City- Wally learns that Zoom has escaped from Ironside, and rushes over to the prison. There he learns that Minerva helped Zoom escape, and killed three guards in the process.

New York- Diana, the current and blinded Wonder Woman, battles Giganta. It appears that Wonder Woman may have met her match but then Wally shows up and distracts Giganta long enough for Diana to knock her out.

The Themysciran Embassy- Wally asks Diana to help him track down Cheetah. Diana agrees but Wally has to take the blinded Wonder Woman with him.

Central City- Captain Cold tries to figure out who Owen Mercer's mother is. His investigation is put on hold when Weather Wizard arrives with a note. The note is a challenge from the Top, his rouges versus Cold's rouges.

Boston- Zoom tries to teach Cheetah how to unlock her true potential, and comes to the conclusion to be her best she must be the only Cheetah.

Later Flash and Wonder Woman track Zoom and Cheetah to the home of Priscilla Rich. Wally find Priscilla's lifeless body. Before the heroes can do anything they are ambushed by Zoom and a super speed Cheetah.

Continued in Wonder Woman #214

description:
Overview

Wally West's family and allies take sides as he weighs an opportunity to profit from his powers at the risk of the precious Flash legacy. Meanwhile, the increasingly powerful media-villain Spin molds intangible mass anxiety into solid unstoppable force against the Flash!

Plot Summary

- Wally is understandably worried about his actions of the last issue. So too are the citizens of Keystone, who are questioning their trust in the Scarlet Speedster.

- Jay appears on a talk show, defending The Flash and revealing that all the stolen money and credit cards have been returned. The host keeps on placing the blame on The Flash, and at the behest of the show's director, who appears to have a connection to the mysterious creature that Spin is using to channel his powers, brings up the two children that Flash has been running around with lately.

- The Justice League decides not get involved officially and to let Wally handle his own problems for now. His old friend Roy Harper, formerly Speedy and currently Red Arrow, decides to pay Wally a visit.

- The Flash answers the ad from last issue and meets Mike Virgil. Apparently a telekinetic, and a seller of rare antique pop-culture memorabilia, Virgil hires Flash to watch a DVD that no one has ever been able to decode due to it's speed. Flash's powers should allow him to watch the disc in slow motion.

- Jay, under the influence of Spin, uses the vibrational leash between Iris, Jai and Wally to "pull" Wally to them. When Jay strikes Wally, the kids begin to defend their father.

- Before the fight really starts, it's broken up courtesy of a flare arrow from Roy. This disrupts Spin's control over Jay, and he and the Wests speed off to the television station to investigate, leaving Red Arrow in their dust.

- Spin's accomplice, now identified as Edwar, tells him The Flash is coming. Spin reveals more of their relationship. He gives Edwar emotion, and Edwar in turn gives him power. Spin asks Edwar to summon an anxiety they can use to defeat Flash. When it materializes, it's big, hairy, and decidedly simian...
name: Fast Money, Part Two

description: Get ready for the race you've all been waiting for: Superman vs. The Flash! The JLA doesn't like being left in the dark when it comes to their members' personal lives...especially when a longtime teammate refuses to divulge his true identity. But Flash doesn't have time to hang around the Watchtower while Keystone City is in trouble, so it's up to Superman to bring him back!

description:
Primate fear! Estranged from Jay Garrick, The Flash is brutally double-teamed by the return of the one foe able to outdo Spin's psychic rampage with one of his own — Grodd! Meanwhile, a lowlife strikeforce, one with strangely cosmic trappings, targets the twins' fantastically developing powers! Four generations of the Flash legacy anchor this special issue!

Spin might have made a bad decision in bringing Gorilla Grodd to help him combat the Flash. The super-powered simian doesn't like being told what to do, and he takes out his anger on Spin.

Wally, Jay and the twins arrive at the television station where they've tracked Spin. Wally begins to argue with the talk show host who's been slandering his name, before Iris points out they're being filmed.

Meanwhile, two odd-looking individuals argue about their failure to capture two "Forever People." Brother Think and Brother Drive use other, different but familiar sounding, terminology like ""Boom Drive," "Sister Box," and someone called "Boss Dark Side." They pick up a signal and drive away.

Back at the station, people's anxieties are coming true as a result of the battle between Grodd and Spin. Their fighting brings them right up through the middle of a Keystone street. Jay works to break them up while Wally has his hands full with violent employees. Before Jai and Iris can help, they're scooped in a net trailing behind the vehicle driven by Think and Drive.

Wally finally makes it outside, and takes the fight directly to Grodd, apparently falling to the gorilla's mental powers.

The twins manage to escape the net, but are immediately sedated by Think, who screams "Live for Dark Side! Die for Dark Side!" Taken inside the villain's vehicle, Jai and Iris are locked up and forced to listen to a de-motivational mantra. But while Jai can't break his shackles, the unconscious Iris destroys hers, glowing and shooting off lightening bolts in every direction!
name: Fast Money, Part Three: Broken News

description:
A bold new beginning for The Scarlet Speedster, as new series artist Alberto Dose makes his debut! In the aftermath of the most horrific attack on The Flash ever, the Fastest Man Alive is nowhere to be found! As Keystone City becomes a breeding ground for lethal street races and rogues, a new type of Flash emerges, a new identity, one we can't say anything else about!

Street racers have taken over the streets of Keystone City, and the cops seem powerless to stop them. The only two who seem to care, Detective Jared Morillo and Detective Fred Chyre are busy trying to solve the murder of Adams Perkins, the Keystone City Police Department's Forensic Scientist, who was frozen to death in the middle of August.

Meanwhile, Wally West, who has no idea he is the Flash, is working the overnight shift as a mechanic for the K.C.P.D. He is enjoying the job and likes his boss, Wheeler, but hates the hours, and isn't sure about Reece, Wheeler's daughter who works in the shop too.

When Wally goes to lunch he meets a strange man named Len, who unknown to Wally is Captain Cold. The pair share a conversation, like they met for the first time, even though they have battled countless times. When Wally gets home, his wife Linda is leaving for school, and implies that there relationship is on the rocks due to the lost of their twins and the hours of Wally's job.

That night as Wally drives to work, he gets an accident, but time seems to freeze and he is able to get the people involved free from danger. Then time starts back up and an explosion launches Wally from the scene. When he wakes up , no one knows what he did. Wally thinks it was all a dream but a strange man give Wally a ring and says "its time to run again" and disappears into the crowd.
name: Ignition, Part One: Driven

description:
"Ignition" continues! The Fastest Man Alive struggles to protect his fellow officers as the true identity of their killer is revealed. The Flash wants to bring the murderer to justice, but so does a rogue outside the law! Plus, a visit from the new rogue profiler for the K.C.P.D. is anything but pleasant for Wally and his wife, Linda!

Wally West has forgotten he is The Flash, but the events of the night before have made him realizes he has some sort of super-speed. After testing the limits of what he can do, he heads back to work at the K.C.P.D garage, where Wheeler, his boss, tells him about the latest cop murdered by being frozen to death. Their conversation is interrupted by Detective Jared Morillo and Alexander Petrov, who get under Wally's skin by mentioning he isn't as good as his uncle Barry Allen.

Wally goes for a walk and some would be muggers try to mug him. Wally tries to use his super-speed, but it doesn't work at first and he gets beaten up. Then when the muggers attempt to shoot him the speed kicks in and Wally is able to catch the bullets. Wally thinks he has the upper hand but the shock waves of his super-speed shake the buildings around him and they crash down on him, pinning him underneath.
name: Ignition, Part Two: Shifting Gears

description:
As the Fastest Man Alive attempts to come to grips with his new identity, a new Rogue announces his presence in Keystone City. But what is his strange connection to The Flash? Plus, meet the new Keystone City Rogue Profiler and see what Captain Cold, Keystone's most wanted man, has been up to!

Wally West, who still doesn't know he is The Flash, digs himself out of the rumble of a fallen building that he accidentally destroyed, while having a uncontrollable burst of super-speed. He then finds the Flash costume that popped out of the ring a stranger gave him days ago. Wally also learns he can heal quickly, and after calling 911 runs off to his favorite dinner to clean his head, and think about what happened.

At the dinner, Wally bumps into Len, a strange man who seems to be at the dinner when ever Wally is there. Unbeknown to Wally, Len is really Captain Cold. Len and Wally talk about Wally and Linda's relationship, but when news that the KCPD has Captain Cold cornered, Len excused himself and Wally leaves soon after.

Seconds later at the warehouse the KCPD have, who they think is Captain Cold cornered, Wally arrives and runs inside. There Wally learns the man the KCPD have trapped is not Captain Cold, but a new villain calling himself Mr. Element. Mr. Element then uses a gun much like Captain Cold to freeze Wally.

Meanwhile in the KCPD garage that Wally works at the newest Rogue Profiler Doctor Ashley Zolomon comes looking for Wally West.
name: Ignition, Part Three: Crash & Burn

description:
"Ignition," Part 4 of 6. As the rash of police officers frozen to death continues, someone close to Wally West becomes the next target! Trying to come to grips with who and what he is, our hero goes on the hunt for Captain Cold - the most wanted man in Keystone City - hoping to stop him before another cop is put "on ice!"

Captain Cold finds the body of Wally West, who doesn't remember he is the real Flash, frozen in a block of ice. Wally is alive and Cold takes the body before the KCPD can stop him. Cold then takes Wally to the ice rink to thaw him out and talk to him. Cold tries to convince Wally that he is innocent in the freezing deaths of several cops. Wally believes him, but still tries to take him in for questioning. Cold escapes and Wally is left wondering whats going on.

Back at the KCPD headquarters, Wally meets with Doctor Ashley Zolomon who wants to apologize for what her husband did, but Wally doesn't want to hear it. Later that night Wally returns home to find the Batman waiting for him.
name: Ignition, Part Four: Cold Reality

description:
Wally West is about to learn that having a secret identity isn't all it's cracked up to be when he's accused of a crime by Keystone Police. But as the Flash tries to clear Wally's name, an old villain stops him and all of Keystone dead cold. Meet the Slowest Man Alive: The Turtle!

Mirror Master is caught by Captain Cold, using drugs, and if forced to promise to never use them again.

Wally West is being questioned by detectives Chyre and Morillo about the apparent attempted murder of Ashley Zolomon. But during the question times seems to stop. Wally soon learns the Turtle has gained a new power. He can steal the speed force from almost anything, and is using it to wander the streets of Central City and make everyone move as slow as him.

Meanwhile in Chicago, Captain Boomerang begs Heatwave to lend him some money for a big score.

Back in Central City, Wally defeats Turtle and goes back to the detectives, he learns Ashley's car's brakes didn't work and she crashed. He later realizes it was because he forgot to put a piece back in her car while he was repairing it.

Later in Ashley's hospital room she is visited by Zoom, and a radio announces the death of Sue Dibny, leading into Identity Crisis.
name: Slow Motion

description: A Rogue Profile on the reformed villain Mick Rory, a.k.a. Heat Wave! Find out what drove Heat Wave to a life of fire and crime, and what's drawing him back in. James Jesse has a mission for Heat Wave: take down the killer Murmur and prove he still has what it takes to join the FBI. But little does Heat Wave realize, he's about to become a catalyst for what soon will be known as...Rogue War!

description:
A exciting new creative team comes aboard as THE FLASH speeds toward . . . the end? The past always seems to catch up with the Fastest Man Alive, and as Infinite Crisis approaches, Wally West reflects on his life with his wife and kids and sees that the end may be near.

Wally wakes up from nightmares involving him and his twins, to learn that his in-laws are visiting. During breakfast, Wally's mother in-law convinces him to check out their new church, so that his can get some spirtal guidance for the twins.

At the church, Wally has to change into the Flash to save some people from falling scaffolding. During his rescuing, Wally notice a small boy demonstrate super strength, but by the time Wally goes to find the boy his has disappeared.

Wally soon finds the boy in the basement of the church with several other meta-human children. One boy explains that they are really all from an other dimension where everyone has super powers and the there is no crime. There is though, sickness and the children need an item called the Summoner to heal their dieing dimension. Wally is too eager to help and races off to find the Summoner.

After Wally leaves a mysterious voice tells the children they have done good and there will be a place for them in the "new" world.
name: Finish Line 1

description:
The extraordinary tale 'Finish Line' continues as Nightwing tries to help Wally piece together the clues to who's behind the evil threatening the West family. Is the end near for Wally?

The Flash goes to the Flash Museum to retrieve a piece of alien tech called The Summoner. The Summoner can be used to save a race of inter-dimensional traveling children who each possess super human abilities. At the museum the Flash learns that the Summoner is missing and calls on his friend Nightwing to help him investigate.

The trail leads to Cyborg and STAR Labs. Cyborg warns Flash that he and STAR Labs just stopped someone from stealing the Summoner and to be careful with trusting the traveling children. Wally is thinking of his twins when he takes the Summoner to the children.

There he watches as the children heal one of their own and then watches in horror as Wally learns that he has been tricked. The traveling children real worship Vandal Savage, and his blood gave them the powers they show Wally. Whats worse is Savage has captured Bart and Jay.
name: Finish Line 2

description:
Part 3 of the explosive story 'Finish Line' brings the Fastest Man Alive face-to-face with one of the deadliest mortal enemies for all generations of the Flash: the immortal killer Vandal Savage!

Wally West, Bart Allen and Jay Garrick are all captured by Vandal Savage, who is now in possession of the Summoner, a weapon he plans on using to crash a meteorite into Earth. After the three Flashes escape they split up.

Bart rushes around the city calming people and putting out fires that are being caused by the meteorite nearing Earth. Jay races off to find Linda West and tell her that Wally is okay. Wally heads right at Savage but is blindsided by one of Savage's followers and knock unconscious.
name: Finish Line 3

description:
Vandal Savage may be successful in his ambition to bring about the end of mankind's days on planet Earth. Can Wally West save him, or are these his final days as well?

Wally has a vision of the the future if Vandal succeeds in crashing the Thanatos, a huge meteor, into Earth and it does not look good. So when he wakes up he tries to subdue Vandal's followers, but it is not until Morillo and Chyre show up that things look promising. Then with the help of Myles Wally is able to reverse the The Summoner beam and send Thanatos back into space. As a last ditch effort to stop the Flash, Vandal gets in the way of the beam and gets sent into space as well.

With Vandal gone his followers start to lose their powers and go back to normal. Wally then races home where he decides to hang up the uniform for a while and concentrate on being a father.
name: Finish Line 4: The End

description:
The Flash takes the twins to Gorilla City on their first international mission, and the round-the-world trip becomes an adventure in itself! Plus, the upheavals at Keystone News result in a huge discovery — one that could blow the Wests' cover for good!

Iris is becoming older and older every second and Flash, partly under control by Grodd, searches for Nzame, the gorilla healer, while trying to find a cure for his daughter.
